	   <a name=103135173778698></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103135173778698><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6278&mid=103135173778698>Best BP? Not really.</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6278&mid=103135173778698#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=164398><span id= >Khift</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>39 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 6th 6:49 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Is this the best BP in Eq? No, not really. Is it an awesome piece of armor? Hell yeah. It &lt;i&gt;is&lt;/i&gt; arguably the best 'Uber' BP when you are speaking about availability, but best total? No.<br><br>I would personally say that this is the 4th best BP in Eq. As for a list of what I consider the best, look below.<br><br>1. Great Shadow Platemail, +80 Ac, +25 Sta, +125 HP, +30 to SVFIR and SVCOLD, drops off of Aten Ha Ra<br>2. Heavy Yttrium Breastplate, +75 Ac, +20 Sta, +100 HP, +30 to SVFIR and SVPOS, drops off of Lord Inquisitor Seru<br>3. Breastplate of the Void, +65 Ac, +25 Sta, +125 HP, effect of Heart of the Void*, +8 to all SV's, drops off of Vyz'Hydra the Cursed<br>4. Breastplate of Eradication, +55 Ac, +20 Sta, +100 Hp, +8 to all SV's, drops off of the Statue of Rallos Zek<br><br>*As for the proc on BPotV, it adds 225 HPs, but does not stack with Shaman HP buffs, meaning that spells such as Khura Focusing (60), which adds 430 HPs, Talisman of Kragg (55), which adds 365-380 HPs and Harnessing of Spirit (49), which adds 248-250 HPs. So, thusly, seeing as most raids buff their MT with at least one of those 3 spells, it isn't truly worth it to sacrifice those 23-205 HPs, so I did not include that in my considerations.<br><br>So, although this BP rawks and is alot more accessible than the other 3, it is NOT the best. I still wouldn't turn it down on a raid though =P.<br>&nbsp;<br>A sunflower scowls at you, ready to attack -- what would you like your tombstone to say?<br>A sunflower kicks YOU for 22 damage!<br><br>Varukisas Jadescale, 40th Iksar Monk<br>Tarew Marr<br>&lt;House of Elder&gt</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
