	   <a name=1036559234830></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f1036559234830><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6278&mid=1036559234830>RE: why?</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6278&mid=1036559234830#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=7370><span id= >Aren</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>50 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Nov 6th 12:27 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.31]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>My Guilds point system works like this:<br><br>All members were given points to start based on time in guild to a maximum of 11, 1 point per month in guild.<br><br>Then all loot we could possibly attain is given a point value.<br><br>Vindi BP and this BP are 50 points.<br>HoT armor is 5-20points<br>etc etc.<br><br>When an item drops, all people who want it send a tell to the loot master, loot master checks point lists, and person with the Highest point total recieves the loot, and has the value deducted from his points (you can go negative if you are the highest who bid on item)<br><br>At the end of the raid, all points spent are added up, and divided among all attendees.<br><br>So, on a HoT raid with lots of armor, say 20 people were there, and 60 points were spent on loot. Each person in attendance would recieve 3 points.<br><br>In ties you would roll etc.<br><br>seems to work so far, the people who attend the most raids, get the most points and therefore, most loot.<br><br>Rewards participation, but has drawbacks.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
